  "Information Technology Club"

  "Woah- this one sounds more interesting."

  "It's literally the name of a school subject, Mikoto."

  "Ah, right, we had that in the entrance exam, too... So this should be a club
  about computers..." Mikoto pondered, then turned to her blonde friend, "Mona!
  You were somewhat nerdy, so maybe computers might be your forte!"

  "My dad has one, but all that I've touched it for was just my IT
  assignments..." Mona reluctantly replied in a seemingly apologetic tone.

  "Oh- you don't have to feel bad about it, Mona... Anyway, we're going in now."
  Mikoto knocked the clubroom door, "Excuse me, we are here to check the club!"

  The door opened, revealed a male student shorter than the three girls,

  "Wel...come to the Information Technology Club!" The boy said in an
  almost-unhearable tone.
